lenders.name: Robert
lenders.occupational_info:
I am working as a website developer for a New York Personal Injury Law Firm. NY is reported to be a very busy state and several dangerous accidents validate this. According to the NHSTA, an accident occurs every 10 seconds somewhere in the US due to negligent driving, driving dangerously, or driving under the influence of banned and lethal drugs.

In some accidents, no physical injuries are caused but one can still ask for compensation for physical damages to the car and get the repair expenses, but in accidents where occupants are physically injured then a personal injury lawsuit can be filed against the negligent driver or any other person responsible for the accident/injuries.

Most of the accidents involving heavy vehicles like trucks, tractor-trailers cause serious personal injuries or are fatal to the occupants of the smaller vehicles.

Therefore, if you want justice and right compensation for the injuries, then follow these guidelines :- 

a) Ascertain the nature of injuries and damages suffered right after the accident. If anyone is fatally injured including the driver at fault, then ask for medical help right away. Call for an ambulance or the state police at once.

b) File an accident report case in the NY police station and retain a copy of the same. If you are not at fault, then do not admit it. The person responsible for the accident should be handed over to the police.

c) Call a NY car accident lawyer to help in filing an accident injury lawsuit and get compensation for the injuries from negligent individual or authority. If the accident is due to malfunctioning of traffic signals, then a notice can be sent to NY State authorities, as they are responsible for the maintenance of traffic signals. 

d) Collect all the essential facts related to the accident like names, address, and the contact numbers of people involved in the accident.  Also, write down the car description, license plate number, and vehicle identification number to claim the insurance money.

You may contact New York Personal Injury Lawyers at :
The Woolworth Building, 233 Broadway, New York, New York - 10007, Phone : (212) 766-5656
